CSCE 451/851 Homework 3 - Problem 2
Sleeping Stylist with a Custom Monitor

Team members:
Karnav Patel

Build:
make

Run:
./sleepingStylistMon

What to observe:
The program creates 120 customer threads and one stylist thread. The monitor is
implemented in monitor.c and uses POSIX semaphores only. It does not use
pthread condition variables.

The monitor uses:
entry_queue - the monitor entry semaphore
urgent_queue - the signal-and-wait queue used by signaling threads
CV stylistAvailable - customers wait here until the stylist is ready
CV customerAvailable - the stylist waits here when the salon is empty

The output lines beginning with "signal(...)" and "wait(...)" demonstrate the
signal-and-wait discipline. When signal wakes a blocked thread, the signaler
yields on urgent_queue. The awakened thread resumes at the statement after its
wait call and runs inside the monitor before the signaler continues.

The chair line uses the required form:
| 1 | 1 | 1 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 | => 3

The output also reports:
Given haircuts = number of completed haircuts
Salon full = counter incremented by 7 each time the seventh chair is filled
Salon empty = number of times the stylist goes to sleep
CV counts = number of threads blocked on each condition variable

Time spent:
Problem 2: about 8 hours.

Challenge level:
Problem 2: 5 out of 5.
